HEADWORD: Breechloader
<hw>Breech"load`er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A firearm
which receives its load at the breech.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For cavalry, the revolver and <qex>breechloader</qex> will
supersede the saber.</q> <rj><qau>Rep. Sec. War (1860).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Breech-loading</ent>⟦br⟧
